Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.23,0:00:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.94,0:00:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-Over there too!\N-Is it a short?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.73,0:00:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the fire extinguishers! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.17,0:00:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.68,0:00:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My job is to shoot Schuwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.14,0:00:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with this damn fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it now! You got another idea, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.19,0:01:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is better. It's way the hell better!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They're like ants!\NThey're like ants running from the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome! Awesome, Johan!\NThis is magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.43,0:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, pal. Get a look at this too…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.02,0:01:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! The books! The books are burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:01:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're frantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them\Nis scrambling for their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.21,0:02:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you sense their fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.34,0:03:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you can shoot\Nyour first one or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it all comes down to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.43,0:03:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That determines\Nwhether you can use a gun or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever trained with a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.98,0:03:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.74,0:03:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're self-taught then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.61,0:03:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.95,0:03:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never fired a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.83,0:04:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even once?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.03,0:04:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Always make sure you fire twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That dramatically increases\Nthe chances of a kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.55,0:04:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't do that…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.55,0:04:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you're as good as dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.19,0:04:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.57,0:04:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.36,0:04:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're nothing but a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.20,0:04:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All you're good for is giving life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my job to take life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.13,0:04:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.23,0:05:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Always make sure you fire twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like… I'm not hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.00,0:06:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've stopped… trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.51,0:06:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The smoke's in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.27,0:06:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry! I've got to hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.78,0:06:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't get away this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.97,0:07:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't push!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.22,0:07:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This way's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.78,0:07:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.57,0:07:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, stay calm and don't panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow security's directions and calmly--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.83,0:07:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.33,0:07:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All the doors are locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nat least get Mr. Schuwald out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.09,0:07:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes, sir!\N-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.17,0:07:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a way of escaping?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you plan on taking\NMr. Schuwald through the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.77,0:07:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Break down a door!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.85,0:07:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.78,0:08:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the books are burning up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.36,0:08:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks as if the fire\Nwill burn everything down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.53,0:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really all you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you happy just describing\Nthis hellacious scene to me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as if you were reading\None of my books to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't your objective to take my place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.35,0:08:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.47,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I came up with a different idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.86,0:08:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see you're not afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.86,0:08:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.45,0:08:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.30,0:09:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can barely see,\Nbut when I'm this close…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.48,0:09:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you see\Nwhen you look into my eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.90,0:09:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in a town\Nlike those found in fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.74,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people died there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.16,0:09:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I left,\NI walked hand-in-hand with the other me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.05,0:09:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if\Nthere were only us two in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.80,0:09:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither of us had names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.47,0:10:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.82,0:10:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, do you know this lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.37,0:11:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.98,0:11:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, I forgot some papers.\NI'd like you to go and get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.90,0:11:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go to the estate and get them.\NThey're on the desk in my study.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.53,0:11:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,These must be them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:11:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Report on the Investigation\Ninto the Death of Margot Langer."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hellfritsch Detective Agency."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Margot Langer.\NReal name: Helenka Nováková."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.45,0:12:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Born in Prague, Czechoslovakia\NAugust 12, 1955."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Illegally immigrated to former\NWest Germany in 1970 at age 15."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"In Munich, she worked as\Na high-class call girl serving
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.76,0:12:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mainly men in political\Nand financial circles."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.68,0:12:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"She became well-known\Nin high society, though only in private."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"The client who requested\Nthis investigation, Hans Georg Schuwald,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was also one of her customers."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.36,0:13:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Dad, you were still looking for Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"At age 22, she gave birth\Nto Mr. Schuwald's child."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.91,0:13:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"The boy was named… Karl."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.29,0:13:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, I want you to listen\Nvery carefully to what I'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.59,0:13:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this money\Nand get on the train on platform five.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.18,0:13:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.97,0:13:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't! If you stay with me,\Nyou'll be sent away to some institution!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.52,0:13:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay, you'll always\Nbe called the son of a whore!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.65,0:13:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They said Dad abandoned me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't abandon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.62,0:13:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I don't hate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:13:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.14,0:14:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.93,0:14:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"The boy stayed with\Nseveral foster families."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"Some were not good,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but some were excellent."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.65,0:14:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He was always alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.78,0:14:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt that was written down anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"Margot Langer continued to be\None of the best high-class call girls."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.46,0:14:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"She retired in 1992."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"There are rumors that she was lovers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.92,0:14:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with the head of an underground bank\Njust before she quit."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.26,0:14:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"We were unable to confirm the rumors."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.43,0:14:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"The underground bank laundered money\Nfor the German black market
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for five years from 1991."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:15:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"They were known to be\Nthe only organization
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.98,0:15:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that turned illegal proceeds into\Nlegal funds for the underworld."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"After retiring,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the call girl Margot Langer\Nlived in Offenbach, Hesse."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is a photo\Nof the apartment she lived in then."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.46,0:15:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"A young man aged 18 lived with her." 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"The nature of their relationship\Nis unknown."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.43,0:15:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"On November 2, 1995,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer was found murdered\Non Heide Street."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.73,0:15:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"According to the police report,\Nshe was the victim of a random killing."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.23,0:15:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"The murderer was never arrested."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.99,0:15:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.91,0:15:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"We have obtained\Na letter Margot Langer sent to a friend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.95,0:15:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,three months before her death."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.25,0:15:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"A copy is enclosed."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.92,0:16:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mom's writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.47,0:16:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,After retiring,\NI now live a very quiet life here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.94,0:16:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In this peaceful life,\NI think often about my lost son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think of my friend who tried\Nto escape Czechoslovakia with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.45,0:16:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She was captured at the border\Nand dragged back to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.62,0:16:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that she gave birth to twins\Nand was living a happy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.92,0:16:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That reminds me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.75,0:16:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I recently met a young man\Nwho's about the same age as my lost son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.01,0:16:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This young man looks very much like\Nmy friend in Czechoslovakia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.93,0:16:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When I am with him,\Nit feels as if I'm talking to my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure my boy\Ngrew up to be a fine man like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he is living happily somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.78,0:17:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all right, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no longer alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.33,0:17:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad wanted me to read this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally understand\Nwhat Mom meant when she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.63,0:17:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"I don't hate him."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.22,0:17:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry anymore, Mom. I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.77,0:17:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck is going on?\NEvery darn door's locked shut!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.78,0:17:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, did you call the fire department?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! What the heck is happening\Ninside this darn library?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.23,0:18:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.94,0:19:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-It's open!\N-The door's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.74,0:19:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't panic! Carefully, one at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.95,0:19:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a line and exit orderly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.20,0:19:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Women and the elderly first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.54,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, I don't know how to repay you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.09,0:19:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Two shots left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.13,0:19:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.51,0:20:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.86,0:21:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.86,0:21:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, you shouldn't shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.24,0:21:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.87,0:21:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't! Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.13,0:21:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.45,0:22:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.13,0:22:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.14,0:23:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by: Brian Athey
